==English==

===Etymology===
{{L.}} ''[[calculus#Latin|calculus]]'', [[pebble]] (used for counting), diminutive of ''[[calx#Latin|calx]]'', [[limestone]], + diminutive suffix ''[[-ulus]]''

===Noun===
{{wikipedia}}
{{en-noun|calculi|-}}

# {{countable}} {{mathematics}} Any formal system in which [[symbolic expression]]s are manipulated according to fixed rules.
#:''vector calculus''
# {{uncountable}} {{analysis}} [[differential calculus|Differential calculus]] and [[integral calculus]] considered as a single subject.
# {{countable}} {{medicine}} A stony [[concretion]] that forms in a bodily organ.
#:''renal calculus'' ( = [[kidney stone]])
# {{uncountable}} (''dentistry'') Deposits of [[calcium phosphate]] salts on teeth.

